

Simple Note Vim Plugin
======================

simple note vim plugin let you create plain text files with an note id in your note
file directory. the note id is auto-generated. for example: `~/notes/01-test.note` ...


Install
=======

    $ make install

or

    $ make link

Options
=======

in your vimrc:

    let g:simpleNoteDir = expand('~/your_note_dir')

Command
=======

- AddNote
- AddNote [title]


